{"lemma":"أَدْخِنَةُ","slug":"أَدْخِنَةُ","root":"د.خ.ن","root_slug":"د-خ-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/د-خ-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دُخان","root":"دخن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12297","n12298"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%92%D8%AE%D9%90%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"smoke"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"steam"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tobacco"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evil, mischief","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dearth, drought, sterility, unfruitfulness, hunger","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Attested since 475 CE, according to the Doha Dictionary.\nHas been hypothesized to be borrowed from Middle Persian *dūd xān or *dūd xānag continued in Dari دود خانه (dūd-xāna, “smoke-room, the compartment of a house below a chimney; family, house, = دودمان (dūdmān)”)."},"ipa":["/du.xaːn/","/dux.xaːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12297","headword_ar":"دُخَانٌ","root":"dxn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dux~aAnN","text_ar":"دُخَّانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which latter is the form [now] commonly used, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxanN","text_ar":"دَخَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuvaAnN","text_ar":"عُثَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a less usual term, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Smoke"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K: [in the S it is said merely that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxaAn","text_ar":"دُخَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of fire is well known:]) pl. (of the first, S, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAxinu","text_ar":"دَوَاخِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAvinu","text_ar":"عَوَاثِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuvaAnN","text_ar":"عُثَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) the only other instance of the kind, (Msb,) deviating from rule, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAxiynu","text_ar":"دَوَاخِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [also irreg., and both pls. of mult.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoxinapN","text_ar":"اَدْخِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.]. (K.) [Hence, the tribes of] Ghanee and Báhileh ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiY~","text_ar":"غَنِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAhilap","text_ar":"بَاهِلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") were called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonaA duxaAnK","text_ar":"اِبْنَا دُخَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sons of smoke"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, TA) because they smoked a party of men ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dax~anuwA EalaY qawomK","text_ar":"دَخَّنُوا عَلَى قَوْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":") in a cave and so killed them. (TA.) Hence also, (S,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudonapN EalaY daxanK","text_ar":"هُدْنَةٌ عَلَى دَخَنٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calm"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"truce"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a cause other than recon-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":862},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ciliation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lagalabapK","text_ar":"لَغَلَبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEil~apK","text_ar":"لِعِلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or (assumed tropical:)  [as a cloak]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concealing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inward corruptness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxinati","text_ar":"دَخِنَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAru","text_ar":"النَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"explained above; [see 1;] (Msb;) [for] IAth says that it likens inward corruptness beneath outward rectitude to the smoke [or smoking] of fresh, or moist, firewood: (TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon latent rancour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malevolence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hdn","text_ar":"هدن"},{"kind":"text","text":":) but A'Obeyd, in explaining a trad. in which it occurs, takes it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxanN","text_ar":"دَخَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ a duskiness, or dinginess, inclining to blackness,” in the colour of a beast or of a garment; for he says that it means [a case in which] the mutual love of two parties will not become pure, like the duskiness, or dinginess, that is in the colour of a beast. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxaAnN","text_ar":"دُخَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used by the Arabs for (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"when it arises; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna bayonanaA A^amorN","text_ar":"كَانَ بَيْنَنَا اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@rotafaEa lahu duxaAnN","text_ar":"ا@رْتَفَعَ لَهُ دُخَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There was between us an affair that had evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief, arising in consequence of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  It also means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dearth, drought, sterility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unfruitfulness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so it has been said to mean in the Kur xliv. 9: for it is said that the hungry [once] saw smoke ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxaAn","text_ar":"دُخَان"},{"kind":"text","text":") between him and the sky: or hunger is thus called because of the dryness of the earth in drought, and the rising of the dust, which is likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxaAn","text_ar":"دُخَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly so termed]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [In the present day, it is also applied, but generally pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dux~aAn","text_ar":"دُخَّان","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tobacco; nicotiana tabacum"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n12298","headword_ar":"دُخَّانٌ","root":"dxn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, first and last sentences."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}